divs: sighting detailslocation: vienna, austria over josefsplatz, date: 27\09\2013 (9\27\2013), time: approx. 21:25-22:45 looking out the north-facing windows of a building (the observable sky being only a small area over a courtyard). six individuals witnessed the lights. first one cluster of lights appeared from the north, traveling in a south\southeast direction, and was followed by 4 more clusters (5 in all). they moved slowly and in a straight line. there were virtually no clouds. the lights were observed until they disappeared over the top of our building, directly overhead. they took approx. 2-3 minutes to pass over. several minutes later, clouds had started to drift in and a large beam of light appeared, directly perpendicular to the direction the lights had been traveling, reflecting off the clouds. the beam (possible a searchlight?) remained for approx. 10 minutes.
trends: There have been no other sightings in Vienna
This sighting has never been favorited.
Summary: 5 clusters of lights, greenish-white to orange in color, traveling slowly in a straight line in a S/SE direction.
